@Cathart <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6688022#p6688022">137</a><br>
<br>
I'm curious why you pick Drixx over Freeko. Why is his lack of contribution more damning than Freeko's lack of contribution? I feel the opposite. I.E. I'd rather FoS Freeko at this point.

@Taly:  how many games have you played?<br>
<br>
Be honest.

@Col. Cathart - I use my vote with purpose. It generally stays on the silly RVS vote until I've got someone I'm convinced needs a vote to make him talk, or just needs to be strung up period. I don't move my vote around all over the place generally. Feel free to view my post history and you'll find this fact to be the single absolutely consistent part of my game. It doesn't change no matter what else I might be experimenting with as I try and get better.<br>
<br>
Shall we pick one of the lurksacks to go after Col? I'm game. I shall not wait too long for you to perk up though. Your last three posts have all been more than 24 hours apart!

@Freeko, Day 1 sucks... during Day 1. People change over time. Day 1 usually tells us the most. Tryhards like House and Taly leave lots of evidence and associative tells. No one expects day 1 to be right, especially from me but to argue Day 1 is a useless day is wrong. It really sets the tone.<br>
<br>
I do appeciate parts of the posts where you attempt to outline relationships between players. You mentioned several possible teammates. Can you elaborate there?<br>
<br>
@House, Stop baiting Freeko.

@dragonspawn, because I think there is one scum team though others have brought up the possibilty of two teams, and of course no one bothers to ask who I believed the scum likely were. And no, not everyone is scum in my eyes. If you read it again I make a very clear distinction between one and the other. I do have a few non-scum reads along with scum reads. Of course with your blinders on, you cannot see any of that.<br>
<br>
@Titus, sorry I dont have the game figured out just yet as to exactly who is scum and who is not. Since scum have daytalk in this game they can coordinate how they want to approach a situation, like the wildfire I caused for example by splitting themselves into ones who want to avoid it and others who will willingly be party to it, or provoke it outright. 13 people tells me likely 3 scum in a group and 1 more scum that may not be related to them is about the best guess for what I would think the whole breakdown to be. <br>
<br>
Like I mentioned before, I think dragonspawn is the scum that is getting involved in the wildfire and Shinobi the one that is getting away from it as fast as possible. House I refuse to acknowledge until day 2 comes around as I am currently biased and cannot fairly evaluate him, though being the lonescum would not be a shocker to me. If I were to complete the group, its either Titus or FA_Q2 that I would pick with FA_Q2 being far more likely. Without anything to really go with on ArcAngel9, I think the possibility is there as well that she is the third one as well.

Holy crap... lots of pages...I obviously did see that last post though.<br>
<br>
@Drixx, If you act like scum, I'll think you're scum. For right now, given how much of a pain in the ass you are acting like I'm electing to avoid you. We haven't interacted already and you're discounting all of my reads as bullshit when they aren't that strong or thought out.

Keep digging your grave deeper House. I'm gonna flip exactly what I said I'm gonna flip.<br>
<br>
@all - There's only one play here which is to lynch me and see my flip. After that you guys have my scum reads, for however much good day 1 reads will help. Best to get it done sooner than later. I'm not likely to absorb an attempted night kill, so I'm perfectly happy with this utility. I gladly go to prove my innocence. 1 to 1 is a fantastic trade for a low utility role.

@Klingon, Yup, I'm the insane cop. Let's go. I tunnel as both alignments my dear.<br>
<br>
@Shinobi, it's weak but it's a starting point. I gotta start somewhere.

@Klingon, me tunnelling is not alignment indicative. Ask anyone here who has experience with me. You oughta know that.<br>
<br>
@Varsoon, why do you think I'm town?

@Taly, it's not absolute.<br>
<br>
In The Walking Dead, the scum traitor faked a guilty on actual scum. A cop and a tracker is a little much, unless everyone else is a VT probably.

After this and the large theme (or if we are dead in both) I will take you up on your offer to discuss, as we cannot impact ongoing.<br>
<br>
@Drixx/KC/Taly/Varsoon, to be clear, I want names no reasons.

@Elbrin, am I off on Taly?<br>
<br>
